properties.name: UCL - The Bartlett School of Architecture
properties.description: This refurbishment and extension to University College London’s 22 Gordon Street provides an environmentally responsible home for the prestigious Bartlett School of Architecture. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

properties.name: Guildhall Yard
properties.description: Grade I listed medieval civic architecture, located above the 2nd century Roman amphitheatre, the outline of the arena is outlined by a black oval on the Yard floor. Guildhall Yard is a publicly accessible space.

properties.name: Aldgate Square
properties.description: At the centre of this publicly accessible square is a pavilion with an asymmetrical steel structure and sliding glass walls set between three triangular support points. Over time, the roof will oxidise and eventually turn orange and brown.

properties.name: Trent Park
properties.description: A truly exquisite Grade II country mansion designed in the early Georgian style, nestling in a 413-acre estate of stunning open parklands, woods, and historic landscaped gardens has been meticulously refurbished by Berkeley.

properties.name: Luxmore Gardens
properties.description: Self-guided walk. Enter Luxmore Gardens via Luxmore St (off Malpas Rd) or one of the two alleyways on Rokeby Rd. Stroll through the park and link up with the Brockley Mews walks or walk to Hilly Fields to begin the 3 Peaks Circular walk.

properties.name: Self-guided Modern Architecture Walk – East Putney
properties.description:
Highlights from Putney Society's Modern Architecture Gazetteer in a self-guided walk in East Putney.
Download or print   https://www.putneysociety.org.uk/putney_society_files/Buildings-Panel/Modern_Architecture_Walk_1_Putney_East.pdf

properties.name: Self-guided Modern Architecture Walk – Putney Heath
properties.description:
Highlights from the Putney Society's Modern Architecture Gazetteer in a self-guided walk around Putney Heath.
Start Portsmouth Road and finish Green Man PH.

properties.name: Self-guided Hanger Hill (Haymills) Estate Walk
properties.description: Rare amongst 1930s London suburbs for a large number of modern movement residences in buildings designed by a single practice (Welch, Lander & Cachemaille-Day) as a series of concentric crescents.

properties.name: Self-guided Evidences of the Black Presence in Hackney
properties.description: A number of places testify to the Black Presence in Hackney. These are at some distance from each other. Visiting them would require time and transport but there are frequent bus services.

properties.name: Self-guided River Lee Navigation Walk
properties.description: The Hackney stretch of the historic Lee Valley Navigation is particularly accessible, busy and interesting. Choc-a-bloc with canal moorings, it exemplifies an alternative way of living.

properties.description: This self-guided cycle itinerary has been created by the Open House team to explore exterior architecture in Barking and Dagenham. There are three different routes so you can choose one to suit your cycle abilities.

properties.name: Self-guided Hanger Hill Garden Estate Walk
properties.description: Designated a conservation area in 1969 – one of the first in Britain. Built between 1928 and 1936 the Estate houses and flats are all in the Tudor half-timbered style of architecture within a formal landscape setting.

properties.name: The High Cross
properties.description: Former public conveniences with an array of internal and external original features

properties.name: BCA Barnes Trail - self-guided walk
properties.description: This is a self-guided 2.3 mile circular trail - with a 3 mile extension - and has been designed to show Barnes at its best - just follow the silver 'Barnes trail' discs in the ground. The oar signs en route tell you what to look for.

properties.name: Meridian Water Art - Self Guided Tour
properties.description: A self-guided walking tour of three new artworks on hoarding surrounding the first phase of the £6 billion Meridian Water project. This self-guided tour compliments a separate walking tour with artist Adam David.

properties.name: Albany Park River Restoration Self-guided Tour
properties.description: Self-guided tour around a recently completed river restoration and wetlands project in Albany Park

properties.name: Barons Court and West Kensington self guided walk
properties.description: This walk compiled by Fulham Society experts covers an area developed around the turn of the nineteenth/twentieth centuries and colonised for an eclectic mix of artistic people, commercial uses and a little known cemetery.

properties.name: Brasted Close
properties.description: This project for 11 homes is the result of a campaign by local people to build affordable homes on surplus council-owned land, and will be among the first CLT homes completed in London. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

properties.name: Covent Garden Market
properties.description: This iconic London destination has been managed for the past 15 years by Capital and Counties with a hands-on approach, and operational support from Incentive FM. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

properties.name: Liverpool Everyman Theatre
properties.description: A Stirling Prize-winning project from masters of theatre design, Haworth Tompkins, which is now a key example in their internal post-occupancy led learning, developing future practice. Shortlisted for the Open City Stewardship Awards 2021.

properties.name: Neighbourhood Walks and Heritage Walks
properties.description: Explore Croydon and learn about your local area with illustrated walks that you can print at home. Accessed here: http://www.croydon.gov.uk/walks

properties.name: C20 x Open House Festival Self-Guided tour – Buildings at Risk
properties.description: As an introduction to our work, we invite you to visit some of our recent Buildings at Risk. This is a small selection of examples in London, that can be visited from the outside and that are walking distance from each other.
